# Supabase Edge Functions — Core Reference

---

## Hard Limits (know these before building)

| Limit | Free | Pro | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| CPU time per request | 2 seconds | 2 seconds | Actual computation — NOT wall clock. Most hit limit. |
| Wall-clock timeout | 150 seconds | 150 seconds | Total request time including DB/API waits |
| Background task timeout | 150 seconds | 400 seconds | After response sent (EdgeRuntime.waitUntil) |
| Memory | 150 MB | 150 MB | OOM = function killed, returns 546 |
| Bundle size | 20 MB | 20 MB | After bundling all imports |
| Request body | 2 MB | 2 MB | Use Storage for larger payloads |
| Invocations free tier | 500K/month | unlimited | |

### Error codes you will see

| Code | Meaning | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `546` | CPU or memory limit exceeded | Move work to background task, use built-in AI model, reduce computation |
| `504` | Wall-clock timeout (150s) | Break into smaller tasks, use background tasks |
| `500` | Unhandled exception in function | Add try/catch, check logs |
| `401` | JWT validation failed | Check Authorization header format, or use --no-verify-jwt |

### Active Breaking Changes (March 2026)

```
1. Recursion rate limit: 5,000 requests/minute for function-to-function calls
   If your app chains Edge Functions (Function A calls Function B), this limit applies.
   Error: 429 Too Many Requests with code EDGE_FUNCTION_RECURSION_RATE_LIMIT_REACHED
   Fix: batch work in one function, use pgmq queues for fan-out patterns instead

2. PostgREST v14: anon key cannot fetch OpenAPI schema endpoint
   GET /rest/v1/ with anon key now returns 401 (was allowed before March 11, 2026)
   If your app fetches the schema for type generation at runtime: switch to service_role
   Or use supabase gen types typescript via CLI instead (preferred)
```

### What you CANNOT do in Edge Functions

```
❌ Write to disk (except /tmp — cleared between invocations)
❌ Send email via SMTP — ports 25 and 587 are blocked (use Resend HTTP API instead)
❌ Serve raw HTML to browsers unless you have a custom domain configured
❌ Use NEXT_PUBLIC_ env vars (those are Next.js build-time vars, not Edge secrets)
❌ Use Node.js APIs directly — must use node: specifier prefix
❌ Long-running background processes without EdgeRuntime.waitUntil()
❌ Name your own secrets with SUPABASE_ prefix (reserved)
```

