## Secrets — How to Actually Set Them

V25 used `Deno.env.get()` but never explained how to create the secrets.

### Pre-populated secrets (available in every function without setup)
```typescript
// These exist automatically — no configuration needed
Deno.env.get('SUPABASE_URL')              // Your project URL
Deno.env.get('SUPABASE_ANON_KEY')         // Public anon key
Deno.env.get('SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY') // Service role key (bypasses RLS)
Deno.env.get('SUPABASE_DB_URL')           // Direct postgres connection string
```

### Adding your own secrets
```bash
# Set a single secret
supabase secrets set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
supabase secrets set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
supabase secrets set RESEND_API_KEY=re_...

# Set multiple from a .env file
supabase secrets set --env-file ./supabase/.env.production

# List all secrets (shows names only, never values)
supabase secrets list

# Delete a secret
supabase secrets unset OPENAI_API_KEY
```

### Local development secrets
```bash
# supabase/functions/.env  — loaded automatically by supabase functions serve
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
```

```typescript
// In your function — same code works locally and in production
const openaiKey = Deno.env.get('OPENAI_API_KEY')
if (!openaiKey) throw new Error('OPENAI_API_KEY not set')
```

