## Regional Invocations — Fix Slow DB Calls

By default, your Edge Function runs closest to the user. Problem: if a user in Tokyo
calls a function that does 10 DB queries, and your DB is in us-east-1, each query
crosses the Pacific — adding 150-200ms per query.

**Fix: pin the function to run in the same region as your DB.**

```typescript
// Option 1 — client passes region header (from Next.js server-side code)
const { data } = await supabase.functions.invoke('my-function', {
  body: { userId },
  headers: { 'x-region': 'us-east-1' },  // use your DB's region
})

// Option 2 — force region in the function's config (supabase/functions/my-function/config.toml)
// [functions.my-function]
// verify_jwt = true
// deployment_region = "us-east-1"

// Find your DB region:
// Dashboard → Settings → General → Region
```

```typescript
// When to use regional invocations:
// ✅ Functions that do many DB queries (3+ roundtrips)
// ✅ Functions that use service_role key (admin operations)
// ✅ Functions invoked from server-side Next.js (not browser — latency already low)
// ❌ Functions that only call external APIs (no DB) — geo-routing is beneficial
// ❌ Static data responses — CDN caching is better
```

