## Deno Import Syntax

Deno has different import conventions from Node.js. Getting these wrong causes
`Module not found` errors that are confusing without knowing Deno specifics.

```typescript
// ✅ npm packages — use npm: specifier (current best practice)
import Stripe from 'npm:stripe@14.21.0'
import { Resend } from 'npm:resend@3.2.0'
import OpenAI from 'npm:openai@4.67.0'

// ✅ Deno standard library — use jsr: specifier
import { createClient } from 'jsr:@supabase/supabase-js@2'
import { join } from 'jsr:@std/path@1'

// ✅ Node built-ins — use node: specifier
import { Buffer } from 'node:buffer'
import { createHash } from 'node:crypto'

// ❌ deno.land/x — DEPRECATED, do not use
import { serve } from 'https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts'  // OLD

// ❌ Bare specifiers — don't work in Deno
import Stripe from 'stripe'  // Node.js style — fails in Deno

// Version pinning — always pin versions for reproducible builds
import Stripe from 'npm:stripe@14'          // pin major version
import Stripe from 'npm:stripe@14.21.0'     // pin exact version (most stable)
```

### Shared utilities between functions — _shared folder
```
supabase/functions/
  _shared/           ← imported by multiple functions
    cors.ts          ← shared CORS headers
    supabase.ts      ← shared client factory
    types.ts         ← shared TypeScript types
  send-email/
    index.ts         ← import from '../_shared/cors.ts'
  process-payment/
    index.ts         ← import from '../_shared/cors.ts'
```

```typescript
// supabase/functions/_shared/cors.ts
export const corsHeaders = {
  'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',
  'Access-Control-Allow-Headers': 'authorization, x-client-info, apikey, content-type',
}

// supabase/functions/send-email/index.ts
import { corsHeaders } from '../_shared/cors.ts'
```

### Function config (supabase/functions/[name]/config.toml)
```toml
[functions.my-function]
verify_jwt = true          # default true — set false for public endpoints
deployment_region = ""     # pin region: "us-east-1", "eu-west-2", etc.
```
